activity.name: Future Problem Solving
activity.description: TJ's Future Problem Solving (FPS) club prepares TJ students to compete in the state and international FPS competitions. FPS competitions consist of teams of 4 people or individuals responding to a future scenario by identifying potential problems and solutions to these problems within the space of two hours. Responding to the scenario requires coherent writing, research about the overriding topic of the future scenario, and superior knowledge of the competition format. Join FPS to make new friends and our members will train you for the three major Spring competitions. We are especially interested in recruiting students in grades 9 and 10.
